[1.8 Database Users and Administrators]
	(1.8.1) Database Users and User interfaces
		- four different types of db-system users
			1) Naive users
				-> interact with the system by using predefined user interfaces, such as web or mobile apps.

				-> forms interface
					+ where the user can fill the fields of the form.

				-> may also view read reports generated from the db.

			2) Application programmers
				-> write app programs.

				-> can choose many tools to develop user interfaces.

			3) Sophisticated users
				-> interact with the system without writing programs.

				-> form their requests using a db query language or by using tools such as data analysis software.

				* Analysts who submit queries to explore data in the db fall in this category.

	(1.8.2 Db Administrator)
		- "DBA" Databse Administrator
			-> has central control over the system

			1) Schema definition

			2) Storage structure and access-method definition

			3) Schema and physical-organization modification
				-> alter the physical organization to improve performance

			4) Granting of authorization for data access

			5) Routine maintenance
				-> backing up the db onto remote servers

				-> ensuring enough free disk space is available

				-> monitoring jobs running on the db and ensuring performance is not degraded by tasks submitted by some users.